{"seq": 656, "ts": "2026-06-23T12:51:38Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-368", "record": {"id": "REQ-368", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Governance Efficiency Benchmark Suite: harness, task definitions, and demo projects for token cost and quality comparison across governance conditions", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-368", "version": 1, "title": "Governance Efficiency Benchmark Suite: harness, task definitions, and demo projects for token cost and quality comparison across governance conditions", "description": "Implement scripts/govern_bench/ with T1-T7 benchmark task definitions (YAML), a runner harness, LLM-judge module, and demo projects (agentic-todo-api, agentic-cli-tool). Compare six conditions: UNGOVERNED, CONTEXT_ONLY, BMAD_STYLE, OPENSPEC_STYLE, SPECSMITH_LIGHT, SPECSMITH_FULL. Primary metric: cost-of-pass = total_tokens / pass_rate.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": []}}, "prev_hash": "c5a090a604f8b3c26c9c41ec8048ced1c4ee5d7187ff4c1a880d68004ee19e39", "hash": "c1e855b7616e7b7075e7f9596e5d3d5ac986fb175d8fdba27880ccf069a42aac", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 657, "ts": "2026-06-25T02:50:05Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-369", "record": {"id": "REQ-369", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Scaffolded AGENTS.md bootstrap must auto-accept specsmith forward migration without prompting", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-369", "version": 1, "title": "Scaffolded AGENTS.md bootstrap must auto-accept specsmith forward migration without prompting", "description": "The scaffolded `AGENTS.md` template (agents.md.j2) MUST instruct agents to run `specsmith migrate run` unconditionally at session start without any Y/n prompt. The `_maybe_prompt_project_update()` function in cli.py MUST auto-run `run_migration()` silently when the installed specsmith version is newer than the project spec_version, printing the list of updated files without asking for confirmation. No interactive prompt may be shown for forward migration in any code path. The template MUST NOT contain `pip install` instructions for specsmith; `pipx upgrade specsmith` is the only permitted upgrade mechanism.", "source": "user requirement", "status": "accepted", "test_ids": []}}, "prev_hash": "c1e855b7616e7b7075e7f9596e5d3d5ac986fb175d8fdba27880ccf069a42aac", "hash": "f218af9daa04c594e0b6def0a1f19c66aedb8346833a94f9bf9f6233936c7efe", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 658, "ts": "2026-06-25T02:50:05Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-370", "record": {"id": "REQ-370", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Backward migration (downgrade) must be a hard error at every specsmith enforcement layer", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-370", "version": 1, "title": "Backward migration (downgrade) must be a hard error at every specsmith enforcement layer", "description": "When the installed specsmith version is older than the project spec_version (i.e. a downgrade is attempted), ALL of the following MUST produce a hard error with exit code 1 and no file mutations. (1) run_upgrade() in upgrader.py returns UpgradeResult with downgrade_error=True and a descriptive message. (2) run_migration() in updater.py returns an error-prefixed string immediately. (3) _maybe_prompt_project_update() in cli.py prints the error and calls sys.exit(1). (4) the specsmith upgrade --spec-version <older> CLI command detects the downgrade before calling run_upgrade() and exits 1 with an explanatory message. No partial migration may occur. The scaffolded AGENTS.md template MUST state that downgrading specsmith on a governed project is not supported and agents MUST surface the error to the user immediately.", "source": "user requirement", "status": "accepted", "test_ids": []}}, "prev_hash": "f218af9daa04c594e0b6def0a1f19c66aedb8346833a94f9bf9f6233936c7efe", "hash": "ea0a180343f87ab794bea5f1b643d4b3afedd026d548a0aa3a6963e6c25b32a5", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 659, "ts": "2026-06-25T03:00:03Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "TEST-369", "record": {"id": "TEST-369", "kind": "testcase", "status": "active", "label": "Governance Efficiency Benchmark scripts/govern_bench/ directory contains task YAML files and a runner module", "confidence": 0.8, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from testcases.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "TEST-369", "version": 1, "title": "Governance Efficiency Benchmark scripts/govern_bench/ directory contains task YAML files and a runner module", "description": "", "requirement_id": "REQ-368", "type": "integration", "verification_method": "pytest tests/test_migration_direction.py::test_govern_bench_structure — assert scripts/govern_bench/ exists and contains at least one task YAML file and a runner entry-point", "input": {}, "expected_behavior": {}, "confidence": 0.8}}, "prev_hash": "ea0a180343f87ab794bea5f1b643d4b3afedd026d548a0aa3a6963e6c25b32a5", "hash": "34cc50c9d52a39953a297b137b829157b3b47f453fffd8746b411838a6da55ec", "recursion_depth": 0}
